nt: The catalytic cracking refinery in Baku, a unit of Plant No. 229, which has been under construction for several years, is believed to be starting production of B100/130 octane aviation gasoline, generally used by Soviet long-range bombers. Another catalytic cracking plant is under construction in Baku.\n\nThe annual capacity of the completed plant is estimated at 135,000 metric tons of aviation gasoline, about equal to each of the two Lend-Lease plants at Gurev and Orsk. An additional plant may possibly be in operation in Grozny and another is being completed in Krasnovodsk. Two other catalytic cracking refineries, in Kuibyshev and Ufa, are still under construction.\n\nFAR EAST\n\n2. Possible high-level Sino-Soviet conference at Peiping:\n\nBetween 28 February and 4 March, 16 LI-2 transports converged on Peiping from various points, including Irkutsk, Dairen, Mukden, and Chengtu, West China. Special requests for weather reports, and the number of both Russian and Chinese transports indicate that the passengers were important officials. The evidence points to a high-level Sino-Soviet conference", "token_count": 177, "token_end_0based": 176, "token_start_0based": 0, "token_text": "ussr 1 baku catalytic plant believed in production comment the catalytic cracking refinery in baku a unit of plant no 229 which has been under construction for several years is believed to be starting production of b100 130 octane aviation gasoline generally used by soviet long-range bombers another catalytic cracking plant is under construction in baku the annual capacity of the completed plant is estimated at 135 000 metric tons of aviation gasoline about equal to each of the two lend-lease plants at gurev and orsk an additional plant may possibly be in operation in grozny and another is being completed in krasnovodsk two other catalytic cracking refineries in kuibyshev and ufa are still under construction far east 2 possible high-level sino-soviet conference at peiping between 28 february and 4 march 16 li-2 transports converged on peiping from various points including irkutsk dairen mukden and chengtu west china special requests for weather reports and the number of both russian and chinese transports indicate that the passengers were important officials the evidence points to a high-level sino-soviet conference", "unred_source_page": 3}
